[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 935 616 with 81 589 (8.7%) cases reported by China. There are now a total of 854 027 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 207 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 76 876 cases when compared with the data on 31 Mar 2020, with the USA accounting for 26 551 (34.5%), Italy for 4782 (6.2%), Spain for 8195 (10.7%), and Germany for 6173 (8.0%) of the newly confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 91.3% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 23.0% of the global cases of COVID-19. The USA, Italy, and Spain have overtaken China in total numbers of cases and Germany may pass China in 1-2 days. A global total of 47 226 deaths have been reported, 43 910 (93.0%) outside mainland China.

It is now clear that while China has the largest population in the world, and was the original location where the COVID-19 outbreak started, it has markedly reduced transmission to a manageable level, now monitoring all arrivals in the country from outside. South Korea has slowly decreased daily, new case counts hovering around 100 in recent days. The USA is now number one outside China for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Italy is number 2, and Spain is number 3. Iran has slowed down in growth rate and Spain and Turkey have been accelerating. To get an understanding of how rapidly things increase, look at Turkey. The 1st confirmed case was reported on 11 Mar 2020 and in 21 days the country has confirmed 15 679 cases and it now ranks number 10 out of 206 countries/territories in terms of absolute numbers of confirmed cases. - Mod.MPP]

